text.tspan: Outside panel (dotted lines = inner panel parts)
Inside panel (dotted lines = outer panel parts)

6 reusable fasteners needed per tile of wall: half of the 4 to join to its adjacent tiles, and 4 to join the inside+outside panel pair; fastener ports are on left and right sides of the inner walls of the panel.
This design has 6" space between each panel's inner enclosure and the next, where fasteners/pipes/insulation/etc. could go.
Not sure what to do about it being wood; it's consequently not fireproof, which I don't like.
